    <fillTypeCategories>
        <!--
            FIX (Issue #1 - Cannot fill vanilla spreaders with dry fertilizer types):
            The SPREADER category is what FS25 uses to determine which fill types a spreader
            fill unit accepts. Vanilla spreaders ship with "FERTILIZER" already in their
            accepted list. Adding the mod's dry types here ensures ANY spreader that accepts
            the SPREADER category will also accept UREA, AMS, MAP, DAP and POTASH.

            FERTILIZER is included so vanilla spreader fill units (which already accept
            FERTILIZER by default) recognise the extended category and accept mod types.
            Without it, the category exists but vanilla equipment never matches it because
            their XML only references the base FERTILIZER type, not this new category name.
        -->
        <fillTypeCategory name="SPREADER">FERTILIZER UREA AMS MAP DAP POTASH</fillTypeCategory>

        <!--
            LIQUIDFERTILIZER is included for the same reason on the sprayer side - vanilla
            sprayers reference LIQUIDFERTILIZER and need it present so the category is
            matched when isFertilizerApplicator scans supportedFillTypes.
        -->
        <fillTypeCategory name="SPRAYER">LIQUIDFERTILIZER UAN32 UAN28 ANHYDROUS STARTER</fillTypeCategory>
    </fillTypeCategories>

</map>